The paper discusses the use of logic programming techniques for the analysis and verification of Java bytecode, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of meta-programming and program specialization, which are common techniques in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper deals with the verification of program properties such as termination and run-time error freeness, which are topics in logic (cs.LO) and formal methods (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses the verification of resource consumption, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR).
